  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The board of public works today\nserved notice on the Washington\nWater Power Co that it must here.\nafter erect arc lamps in the center\nof the street if it wants to collect\nfor such lamps from the city. This\naction is the outcome of the recent\nplacing of seven arc lights along\nthe Lidgerwood and Aston car lines\nin Lidgerwood, in which the lamps\nare suspended almost against the\npole from which they hang.\n\n\nThe city requires all street lights\nto be placed in the middle of the\nstreet in order to get the best re-\nsuits. 1t seems that the w. w. P.\nmust have been short of poles or\nwire when it hung the new lights\nin Lidgerwood"
    }
  ]
